nodes.bodyText:
@stoobie Thanks for pointing that out. The "New Module" UI is a leftover prototype feature that will need to be removed before Pantheon 2 can go live. For Milestone 2, the only path to get content into Pantheon 2 is via git commit to a repository and then a sync in Pantheon.
To select which content is synced from git, you use the filepath patterns that are defined in pantheon2.yml, which needs to be located at the root of the repository. So that's a manual step but it only needs to be done once, not on every sync.
Does that answer your questions?
